# Booking — Cron Reminders Trigger
# M11-S04: publishes the cron-reminders trigger, dispatched to BookingReminderTriggerHandler and
# AdminScheduleReminderTriggerHandler (M17-S03). In production, Cloud Scheduler publishes the
# same trigger directly to Pub/Sub — this endpoint is the local/manual trigger path only,
# protected by the global InternalApiGuard (X-Internal-Key), not PubSubPushGuard.
# Response is { ok: true } once the trigger is published — it does not wait for the jobs to
# finish. Requires the Pub/Sub emulator running (pnpm infra:up); check backend logs for
# "trigger received by <consumer>" to confirm dispatch.
#
# Prerequisites:
#   1. pnpm infra:up
#   2. pnpm --filter @ikaro/backend run migration:run
#   3. pnpm --filter @ikaro/backend run dev

@baseUrl = {{backendUrl}}

### POST /cron/reminders — publish the cron-reminders trigger
POST {{baseUrl}}/cron/reminders
X-Internal-Key: {{internalKey}}

###
